President Obama announced his intent to nominate Congressman John M. McHugh as Secretary of the Army. McHugh is a nine-term member of the U.S. House of Representatives and has been a leader in national defense policy. He is the Ranking Member of the House Armed Services Committee and has served on various committees related to military personnel and intelligence. McHugh has also been involved with the United States Military Academy at West Point. He has a background in political science and public administration. President Obama praised McHugh's commitment to keeping America's Army well-trained and well-equipped.